nd under the occupation and tutelage of the United States, they returned to the field to create narratives of human difference that supported the new national values of democracy, capitalism, and peace. The 1968 student movement challenged these values, resulting in an all-encompassing attack on objectivity itself. Nonetheless, the legacy of the men of one age lives on in the disciplines they developed and the beliefs they established about human diversity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAnthropologistszJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aAnthropologyzJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aNational characteristics, JapanesexHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial scienceszJapany20th century. 0aSocial scientistszJapanxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Japan.2bisacsh  aIzumi Seiichi.  aculture.  afieldwork.  agenerational biography.  ahistory of knowledge.  ahuman science.  aobjectivity.  arace.  atranswar.  atwentieth-century Japanese history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361062040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503610620423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503610620.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyt